14/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police conducted simultaneous operations in 11 provinces across the country on Friday (May 14th), arresting more than 30 people in connection with the so-called Ergenekon case, an alleged plot to create chaos and topple the government.
According to media reports, authorities raided 37 houses of suspected Ergenekon members, seizing evidence.
(CNN Turk, Hurriyet, Radikal - 14/05/10)
